  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off High regime driven by the US yield surge with US 10Y at 4.667 percent up 0.95 percent, BoJ dovishness, and collapsing WTI oil at 104.3 down 4 percent crushing CAD. AUDUSD is the cleanest short as D1 Neutral flips H4 Strong Sell at -6 with AUDJPY confirming at -0.90 correlation and NZDUSD adding confluence at +0.87 cluster-wide selling pressure. Critical counter-narrative: GBP H4 CSM has surged to 100 versus D1 at 59, a 41-point divergence flagged as the most important short-term signal, with GBPJPY H4 momentum at 80 and GBPUSD H4 rising sharply, making any GBP short the highest-risk trade on the board right now.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: GBPJPY CMP 57 with H4 at 80 accelerating, NZDJPY CMP 57 with both D1 and H4 rising\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nBoJ policy commentary hits USDJPY directly; a softer BoJ tone triggers USDJPY extension toward 160 with CADJPY at +0.67 correlation following\nWTI oil continued selloff pressures USDCAD higher as D1 momentum sits at 74 accelerating and H4 divergence resolves upward\nUS 2Y yield move above 3.65 percent confirms USDCHF H4 Strong Buy signal at +5 and invalidates CHF safe-haven narrative entirely",
